%S A396839 1,2,9,128,3400,134784,7237104,499802112,43000968960,4507728537600,
%T A396839 566027590360320,83954292058423296,14533754172922662912,
%U A396839 2906039348225864073216,664970735166945643008000,172709410125183366746603520,50542885670433967811263463424,16557064272655125221893615386624
%N A396839 G.f. A(x) satisfies n*(n+2)/2 * a(n) = (n+1)^2 * [x^n] A(x)^(1/2) for n > 1.
%C A396839 Given that the limits are finite and greater than zero, lim_{n->oo} a(n)/(n+1)!^2 = 2 * lim_{n->oo} A396838(n)/(n+1)!^2. At n = 1000, a(1000)/1001!^2 = 0.47938858658...
%C A396839 This constant is equal to 0.48082819707871001145880627091906684... - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jun 19 2026
%H A396839 Paul D. Hanna, <a href="/A396839/b396839.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..300</a>
%F A396839 G.f.: A(x) = Sum_{n>=0} a(n)*x^n satisfies the following formulas.
%F A396839 (1) (n+1)^2 * [x^n] A(x)^(1/2) = n*(n+2)/2 * a(n) for n > 1.
%F A396839 (2) a(n) = 2*(n+1)^2 / (n*(n+2)) * A396838(n) for n > 1, where the self-convolution of A396838 equals this sequence.
%e A396839 G.f.: A(x) = 1 + 2*x + 9*x^2 + 128*x^3 + 3400*x^4 + 134784*x^5 + 7237104*x^6 + 499802112*x^7 + 43000968960*x^8 + ...
%e A396839 The square-root of the g.f. A(x) begins
%e A396839 A(x)^(1/2) = 1 + x + 4*x^2 + 60*x^3 + 1632*x^4 + 65520*x^5 + 3544704*x^6 + 245996352*x^7 + ... + A396838(n)*x^n + ...
%e A396839 where n*(n+2)/2 * a(n) = (n+1)^2 * A396838(n) like so
%e A396839   n = 2: 2*4/2 * 9 = 3^2 * 4,
%e A396839   n = 3: 3*5/2 * 128 = 4^2 * 60,
%e A396839   n = 4: 4*6/2 * 3400 = 5^2 * 1632,
%e A396839   n = 5: 5*7/2 * 134784 = 6^2 * 65520,
%e A396839   n = 6: 6*8/2 * 7237104 = 7^2 * 3544704,
%e A396839   n = 7: 7*9/2 * 499802112 = 8^2 * 245996352,
%e A396839   ...
%o A396839 (PARI) \\ returns vector of terms a(k) for k = 0..n
%o A396839 {a(n) = my(A=[1,2]); for(i=1,n-1, A=concat(A,0); m=#A-1;
%o A396839 A[#A] = -2*(m+1)^2 * polcoef(Ser(A)^(1/2),m) ); A}
%Y A396839 Cf. A396808, A396838.
%K A396839 nonn
%O A396839 0,2
%A A396839 _Paul D. Hanna_, Jun 18 2026
